dabas argues that the literary works under scrutiny openly play with and re-think conceptions of ghosts as mere exotic, ethnic ornamentation.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 0aAmerican literaturexAsian American authorsxHistory and criticism. 0aGhosts in literature. 4aAmerica. 4aAmerican Studies. 4aCulture. 4aGhost. 4aLiterary Studies. 4aLiterature. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / American / General.2bisacsh  aAmerica.  aAmerican Studies.  aCulture.  aGhost.  aLiterary Studies.  aLiterature.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2018 Part 2z978311076667708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2018z978311071955008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018 Englishz978311060425208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018z9783110603255oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural and Area Stud. 2018 Englishz978311060418408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural and Area Studies 2018z9783110603187oZDB-23-DKU08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript English Contemporary eBook-Package 2016-2018z978311066154540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783839444498zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783839444498423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783839444498/original  a978-3-11-060418-4  EBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural and Area Stud. 2018 Englishb2018  a978-3-11-060425-2  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018 Englishb2018  a978-3-11-066154-5  transcript English Contemporary eBook-Package 2016-2018c2016d2018  a978-3-11-071955-0  DG Plus eBook-Package 2018b2018  a978-3-11-076667-7  DG Plus PP Package 2018 Part 2